WEBVTT

00:02.561 --> 00:04.461
♪

00:10.327 --> 00:11.510
Aah!

00:16.684 --> 00:19.393
(school bell rings)

00:21.004 --> 00:22.021
(Barney belches)

00:22.931 --> 00:25.274
-(work whistle blows)
-Aah!

00:29.530 --> 00:31.363
(scanner beeps)

00:37.112 --> 00:43.250
(playing blues riff)

00:45.862 --> 00:47.271
(tires screech)

00:47.273 --> 00:48.464
Mm.

00:54.704 --> 00:56.513
(tires screeching)

00:58.708 --> 01:00.392
-(horn and toy horn honk)
-What? Whatcha...

01:00.728 --> 01:02.436
(tires screech)

01:03.455 --> 01:05.455
D'oh!

01:05.457 --> 01:05.672
(tires screech)

01:05.808 --> 01:07.191
(grunts)

01:11.221 --> 01:13.739
(hushed):
Who the hell are these people?

01:16.410 --> 01:18.494
♪

01:23.066 --> 01:26.627
Why you... (frustrated grunting)

01:33.594 --> 01:36.095
Oh, my pâté de campagne!

01:36.097 --> 01:37.821
My "Kick me" sign!

01:37.823 --> 01:39.080
(tires screeching)

01:39.082 --> 01:42.159
Oh, how could she?
Why would she?

01:42.161 --> 01:44.937
So many feelings,
all of them anger.

01:44.939 --> 01:46.163
Must drive them away.

01:46.165 --> 01:48.515
Rage belongs on the road.

01:48.517 --> 01:50.109
(tires screeching)

01:51.687 --> 01:53.003
(growls angrily)

01:53.005 --> 01:54.696
-(shouting gibberish)
-(meowing)

01:56.784 --> 01:58.659
(shouting gibberish)

02:08.687 --> 02:10.278
(tires screeching)

02:10.947 --> 02:13.190
Where the hell's my phone?

02:13.192 --> 02:16.376
Got to express my rage
to the person who enraged me:

02:16.378 --> 02:18.345
my wife.

02:19.974 --> 02:21.557
(people murmuring, shouting)

02:22.551 --> 02:25.702
Marge, I am so, so,

02:25.704 --> 02:28.054
so, so angry.

02:28.056 --> 02:30.056
Anger emoji, skull emoji,

02:30.058 --> 02:32.634
eggplant emoji,
because I hate eggplant.

02:32.636 --> 02:34.653
Fire, fire, fire. Aah!

02:34.655 --> 02:36.363
A fire-fire-fire hydrant!

02:39.142 --> 02:40.717
Okay, Homer, stay calm.

02:40.719 --> 02:43.403
Your seat belt will save you.

02:43.405 --> 02:43.620
Wha?

02:46.725 --> 02:48.725
Thank God I still got my airbag.

02:48.727 --> 02:50.394
Safety first.

02:50.396 --> 02:51.228
Hmm?

02:51.230 --> 02:53.154
-Ah. (snoring)
-(whimpers)

02:53.156 --> 02:55.916
Well, at least I got
shatter-proof glass.

02:55.918 --> 02:57.676
Oh, it's shattering!

02:57.678 --> 03:00.596
(distorted):
D'oh...!

03:04.760 --> 03:06.076
(gasps)

03:06.078 --> 03:08.912
I'm soaring through the air
like an angel,

03:08.914 --> 03:10.414
or a beautiful loogie.

03:10.416 --> 03:13.675
How very majestic
the world looks from up here.

03:13.677 --> 03:15.677
The sky, the ocean,

03:15.679 --> 03:16.719
Ralph.

03:16.721 --> 03:19.698
Bart's bald mommy
is going to die.

03:19.700 --> 03:22.259
That's her problem. (laughs)

03:22.261 --> 03:23.685
FEMALE VOICE:
Homer? Yo, big man.

03:23.687 --> 03:26.020
Now's not the time to chill.

03:26.022 --> 03:27.614
What? Who the hell was that?

03:27.616 --> 03:30.858
It's me, Maggie's
Happy Little Elf doll.

03:30.860 --> 03:32.619
Oh, yeah.

03:32.621 --> 03:33.712
She calls you Goobie-Woo.

03:33.714 --> 03:36.197
Of course she does.
That's my damn name.

03:36.199 --> 03:39.051
Okay. Sheesh, Goobie-Woo.

03:39.053 --> 03:40.961
But how are you talking
right now?

03:40.963 --> 03:42.446
That's a little complicated.

03:42.448 --> 03:44.706
You see, I'm a projection
of your psyche,

03:44.708 --> 03:48.042
and you're in the middle of
a very traumatic life event.

03:48.044 --> 03:50.187
Traumatic? What do you mean?
I feel great.

03:51.640 --> 03:52.973
(humming happily)

03:52.975 --> 03:56.884
Homer. Homer, what you're
currently experiencing

03:56.886 --> 03:59.238
is called
post-traumatic elation.

03:59.240 --> 04:01.147
-Is that like Post Raisin Bran?
-(grunts)

04:01.149 --> 04:03.575
Damn it, man,
you are literally in the middle

04:03.577 --> 04:05.327
of a car accident!

04:06.914 --> 04:08.822
What?! Oh, right.

04:08.824 --> 04:10.231
Let me lay this out.

04:10.233 --> 04:12.158
You and me are gonna use
this car ejection

04:12.160 --> 04:15.161
for some self-reflection,
okay, my brother?

04:15.163 --> 04:16.162
And that journey begins with

04:16.164 --> 04:17.664
finding the source
of your anger.

04:17.666 --> 04:21.760
Now, gaze into that
little piece of glass.

04:23.264 --> 04:26.265
I need a safe-deposit box.
Want to know why?

04:26.267 --> 04:28.100
Well, that's why I got into
banking in the first place,

04:28.102 --> 04:31.011
for the thrilling stories.

04:31.013 --> 04:33.330
Well, this morning,
I was on my break

04:33.332 --> 04:34.472
-at the nuclear power plant...
-Uh-huh.

04:34.474 --> 04:37.000
...so I went and got myself
a bag of chips.

04:37.002 --> 04:39.336
Potato chips.

04:39.338 --> 04:41.280
I feel like I'm at
a story slam right now.

04:41.282 --> 04:44.007
They were so delicious
and salty and chompy,

04:44.009 --> 04:46.526
and before long,
they were all gone.

04:46.528 --> 04:47.193
-No.
-Almost.

04:47.195 --> 04:49.621
Oh, there's a twist?

04:49.623 --> 04:52.032
But then I pulled out this,

04:52.034 --> 04:55.276
a chip that looks exactly like
John Travolta.

04:55.278 --> 04:58.112
And that's why I need
a safe-deposit box,

04:58.114 --> 05:00.966
to protect this treasure
forever.

05:02.361 --> 05:05.137
Oh, don't study opera staging
in Vienna, they said.

05:05.139 --> 05:07.681
Work in a bank, they said.

05:09.793 --> 05:12.869
Mm-hmm. Mr. Simpson,
it looks like your family

05:12.871 --> 05:15.129
already has a safe-deposit box.

05:15.131 --> 05:17.983
Your wife rented it out
over a decade ago.

05:17.985 --> 05:20.635
-Wow, you've got a wife.
-Wha?

05:20.637 --> 05:21.803
Now, I'm not supposed to
show you this,

05:21.805 --> 05:25.157
but lucky for you right now
I'm super high.

05:25.159 --> 05:28.735
"Last will and testament"?

05:28.737 --> 05:30.996
Written by Clarence Bouvier,
your father-in-law.

05:30.998 --> 05:33.890
Marge's dad left a will?

05:33.892 --> 05:34.908
He never told me about that

05:34.910 --> 05:37.727
in the four conversations
we ever had.

05:37.729 --> 05:39.320
It says here he set up a trust

05:39.322 --> 05:42.248
to pay Marge Simpson,
ooh, $1,000 a month.

05:42.250 --> 05:46.678
A thousand dollars? What? No.

05:46.680 --> 05:47.420
No! What?!

05:47.422 --> 05:50.665
No! No? What?

05:50.667 --> 05:51.850
No.

05:51.852 --> 05:53.593
And I can confirm that
your wife has been

05:53.595 --> 05:56.521
receiving that money every month
since her father died.

05:56.523 --> 05:59.024
Marge has been getting
all that money for years,

05:59.026 --> 06:01.084
and she never told me about it.

06:01.086 --> 06:03.253
I-I don't know what to feel.

06:03.255 --> 06:05.255
In these situations,
many of our customers

06:05.257 --> 06:06.365
opt for extreme rage.

06:06.367 --> 06:09.701
Well, I hate to just
follow the crowd, but...

06:09.703 --> 06:10.535
(growling angrily)

06:10.537 --> 06:13.330
(grumbling, muttering)

06:15.100 --> 06:17.525
So that's why I was so mad.

06:17.527 --> 06:18.952
And that's why
I'm even angrier now.

06:18.954 --> 06:22.864
For all these years, Marge has
been hiding money from me.

06:22.866 --> 06:26.109
It's a blatant act of, of, uh...

06:26.111 --> 06:28.294
The term is
"financial infidelity."

06:28.296 --> 06:30.555
And I can see how
you'd be angry.

06:30.557 --> 06:31.948
Oh, thank you.

06:31.967 --> 06:33.558
-But it's the wrong emotion
to feel.
-Damn it.

06:33.560 --> 06:36.119
Homer, I'm gonna help you
work through this anger

06:36.121 --> 06:38.955
so you can find peace.

06:38.957 --> 06:41.641
Aw, work? That sounds like work.

06:41.643 --> 06:42.809
How much time do I have?

06:42.811 --> 06:44.236
I'd say about
point-three seconds

06:44.463 --> 06:47.221
-judging by how fast
you're flying towards that tree.
-Aah!

06:47.223 --> 06:50.817
Oh, my God, we're airborne.

06:50.819 --> 06:52.661
-Whoa!
-(all scream)

06:58.160 --> 06:59.993
I don't know which one
I'm more upset about,

06:59.995 --> 07:01.161
that my wife has been keeping

07:01.163 --> 07:02.754
a secret mountain of cash
from me,

07:02.756 --> 07:06.073
or that I'm about to die
in a stupid, violent car wreck.

07:06.075 --> 07:08.001
Don't make me choose,
Goobie-Woo.

07:08.003 --> 07:09.928
(Homer crying out)

07:09.930 --> 07:11.078
Homer, you're spiraling.

07:11.080 --> 07:13.323
Of course I'm spiraling.

07:13.325 --> 07:15.825
I'm literally flying
through the air.

07:15.827 --> 07:18.328
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

07:18.330 --> 07:21.347
Listen, I know you're feeling
all the feels right now,

07:21.349 --> 07:23.349
but we're getting closer
to the real source of your rage.

07:23.351 --> 07:27.279
What? I'm sorry,
I'm eating my feelings.

07:27.281 --> 07:30.523
Bad Homer. Spit out that food,
and those feelings.

07:30.525 --> 07:33.267
(grunts) What was Marge
spending that money on?

07:33.269 --> 07:36.029
And why did she keep it a secret
from everybody?

07:36.031 --> 07:38.198
LISA:
Um, not everybody, Dad.

07:38.200 --> 07:40.107
I hate to say it,
but we've known about

07:40.109 --> 07:42.127
Mom's secret cash
for quite some time.

07:42.129 --> 07:45.130
Yeah, that's why I laugh myself
to sleep every night.

07:45.132 --> 07:47.799
What? And here I've been
worried sick about

07:47.801 --> 07:49.042
your night giggles.

07:49.044 --> 07:51.303
Let me tell you
how we found out.

07:51.305 --> 07:54.306
<i> I was blowing off steam</i>
<i> one day...</i>

07:58.962 --> 08:02.647
<i> ...and I saw that Mom was</i>
<i> getting $100,000 a month!</i>

08:02.649 --> 08:05.400
<i> LISA:</i>
<i> Then I explained to Bart</i>
<i> how decimal points work.</i>

08:08.213 --> 08:10.897
<i> Then we asked Mom about it,</i>
<i> and she admitted</i>

08:10.899 --> 08:12.324
the whole thing.

08:12.326 --> 08:16.720
So then tell me, why did she
keep the money a secret?

08:16.722 --> 08:17.996
I don't think you can handle it.

08:17.998 --> 08:20.223
-I can handle it.
-Okay.

08:20.225 --> 08:21.891
<i> The reason is...</i>

08:21.910 --> 08:24.669
<i> (imitating Marge):</i>
<i> Your father is</i>
<i> an ape-faced butt monster</i>

08:24.671 --> 08:27.822
<i> who eats booger sandwiches</i>
<i> and also sucks.</i>

08:27.824 --> 08:29.323
(laughs)

08:29.325 --> 08:32.827
Why, you little
unreliable narrator!

08:32.829 --> 08:35.180
Ow! Glass is sharp.

08:35.182 --> 08:38.499
Oh, even my kids knew
I was being fiscally unmanned.

08:38.501 --> 08:40.260
(normal voice):
Okay, got to go, ape face.

08:40.262 --> 08:41.578
See you at your funeral.

08:41.671 --> 08:44.505
We'll be the kids running around
in our nice clothes,

08:44.507 --> 08:47.341
poignantly unaware of
the finality of death.

08:47.343 --> 08:50.529
Oh, that tree can't
get here fast enough.

08:50.531 --> 08:51.604
(straining)

08:51.606 --> 08:53.180
Okay, Michael Phelps,

08:53.182 --> 08:54.366
don't swim to your death
just yet.

08:54.368 --> 08:57.035
Don't you want to find out
what Marge been

08:57.037 --> 08:58.703
spending the money on?

08:58.705 --> 09:00.521
Oh, you bet I do.

09:00.523 --> 09:03.266
Well, that's what I thought.
Give me your best guess.

09:03.268 --> 09:04.284
I want to give her
the benefit of the doubt,

09:04.286 --> 09:08.438
but I can't help
but imagine the worst.

09:08.440 --> 09:11.441
See you later. I'm off to earn
our only source of income.

09:11.443 --> 09:17.130
He's gone. Robo-butler,
bring me a caviar hoagie.

09:17.132 --> 09:21.726
(robotic voice):
My word. This is so expensive.

09:21.728 --> 09:24.045
Mmm. Mmm-mmm.

09:24.047 --> 09:25.897
You know what else
I'm paying for?

09:25.899 --> 09:29.568
Sexy handymen doing chores
around the house.

09:29.570 --> 09:32.462
♪<i> I got this feeling on the</i>
<i>summer day when you were gone</i> ♪

09:32.464 --> 09:35.056
♪<i> I crashed my car</i>
<i> into the bridge</i> ♪

09:35.058 --> 09:37.075
♪<i> I don't care</i> ♪

09:37.077 --> 09:40.061
♪<i> I love it</i> ♪

09:40.063 --> 09:42.063
♪<i> I don't care</i> ♪

09:42.065 --> 09:43.807
♪<i> I love it, I love it...</i> ♪

09:43.809 --> 09:45.308
I don't know which I love more,

09:45.310 --> 09:48.645
being rich or hiding it
from my husband.

09:48.647 --> 09:49.345
(robotic laugh)

09:49.423 --> 09:52.832
Let us mock him through dance.

09:52.834 --> 09:54.384
(rapid mechanical whirring)

09:56.671 --> 09:57.762
♪<i> I love it.</i> ♪

09:57.764 --> 09:58.763
(growling angrily)

09:58.765 --> 10:00.915
-Whew, Homer, I hesitate to ask,

10:00.917 --> 10:02.601
but why does your brain think

10:02.603 --> 10:04.828
that's what Marge is doing
with the money?

10:04.830 --> 10:06.271
Because it's what I'd do.

10:06.273 --> 10:08.014
Except the repairmen would be
my favorite rock stars:

10:08.016 --> 10:10.350
Kiss, Bon Jovi, Men at Work,

10:10.352 --> 10:12.852
because of
their excellent work ethic.

10:12.854 --> 10:14.187
-(grunts)
-Stop!

10:14.189 --> 10:16.522
Your wife is a
much better person than you are,

10:16.524 --> 10:19.676
and she's been using the money
in a very different way.

10:19.678 --> 10:20.860
So no robot butler?

10:20.862 --> 10:23.513
♪<i> You been wasting</i>
<i> all your time</i> ♪

10:23.515 --> 10:25.272
♪<i> Throwing shade at Marge</i> ♪

10:25.274 --> 10:27.700
♪<i> You think behind your back</i>
<i> that, yeah</i> ♪

10:27.702 --> 10:29.294
♪<i> She's been living large</i> ♪

10:29.296 --> 10:33.965
♪<i> Well, I really, really hate</i>
<i> to burst your bubble, boo</i> ♪

10:33.967 --> 10:35.967
♪<i> All this time,</i>
<i> she been spending</i> ♪

10:35.969 --> 10:38.695
-♪<i> All that cash on you</i> ♪
-On me? No way.

10:38.697 --> 10:39.863
I'm sure that-- Huh?

10:39.865 --> 10:41.455
♪<i> Homie, Homer, check your elf</i> ♪

10:41.457 --> 10:42.957
♪<i> You ain't too bright,</i>
<i> I'll explain the sitch</i> ♪

10:42.959 --> 10:46.202
♪<i> All them problems</i>
<i>you think you solved yourself</i> ♪

10:46.204 --> 10:47.312
♪<i> That was Marge, bitch</i> ♪

10:47.314 --> 10:49.539
♪<i> That was Marge,</i>
<i> bitch</i> ♪

10:49.541 --> 10:52.208
♪<i> The time your bar tab</i>
<i> was forgiven by Moe</i> ♪

10:52.210 --> 10:53.634
♪<i> That was Marge, bitch</i> ♪

10:53.636 --> 10:56.729
♪<i> That time Dr. Hibbert</i>
<i> reattached your big toe</i> ♪

10:56.731 --> 10:58.139
♪<i> That was Marge, bitch</i> ♪

10:58.141 --> 11:00.825
♪<i> The time you got off</i>
<i> of that DUI</i> ♪

11:00.827 --> 11:02.235
♪<i> That was Marge, bitch</i> ♪

11:02.237 --> 11:04.645
♪<i> I think by now</i>
<i> you know the reason why</i> ♪

11:04.647 --> 11:06.739
Goobie-Woo in da house!

11:06.741 --> 11:08.315
-Oh, my God.
-Whoo!

11:08.317 --> 11:10.243
All this time, I've been
thinking the worst about Marge,

11:10.245 --> 11:14.822
but she was using the money
to save me.

11:14.824 --> 11:16.582
Ya think?

11:16.584 --> 11:20.586
And she only kept it a secret
to save your dumbass male pride.

11:20.588 --> 11:25.408
♪<i> Well, Goobie-Goobie-Woo,</i>
<i> now I can clearly see</i> ♪

11:25.410 --> 11:27.260
♪<i> I've got the greatest wife</i>
<i> and spouse</i> ♪

11:27.262 --> 11:29.688
♪<i> That there could ever be</i> ♪

11:29.690 --> 11:31.097
♪<i> And what's more...</i> ♪
Huh?

11:31.099 --> 11:33.340
Holy crap,
I just flew past the tree!

11:33.342 --> 11:35.268
♪<i> You're gonna live, bitch</i> ♪

11:35.270 --> 11:37.696
♪<i> You're gonna live,</i>
<i> bitch</i> ♪

11:37.698 --> 11:39.255
♪<i> You're gonna live, bitch</i> ♪

11:39.257 --> 11:41.107
♪<i> Yeah, I'm gonna live.</i> ♪

11:41.109 --> 11:42.367
-(laughs)
-Whoo!

11:42.369 --> 11:45.428
Thank God, I don't have to
be mad at Marge anymore.

11:45.430 --> 11:48.431
If anything, you should be mad
at Marge's dad.

11:48.433 --> 11:51.042
-Huh?
-Oh, snap,
I shouldn't have said that.

11:51.044 --> 11:52.043
"Oh, snap"?
What do you mean, "Oh, snap"?

11:52.045 --> 11:54.713
Oh, snap, why not?
What do you know?

11:54.715 --> 11:57.106
Nothing. And closure! (chuckles)

11:57.108 --> 11:59.200
Closure-closure,
closure-closure.

11:59.202 --> 12:01.535
Oh, no. I got to know
what Marge's dad did,

12:01.537 --> 12:02.795
or said or rapped.

12:02.797 --> 12:07.283
Aha, and I've got
the magical footage right here.

12:07.285 --> 12:09.619
Don't look at it!
You've come so far.

12:09.621 --> 12:12.063
Inner peace has almost defeated
your outer rage.

12:12.065 --> 12:14.307
You've got to be strong, man.

12:14.309 --> 12:16.626
So if I look at
that piece of glass,

12:16.628 --> 12:17.902
I could change my fate

12:17.904 --> 12:19.887
and perhaps even risk
my very soul?

12:19.889 --> 12:22.389
Well, I'm cool with that.

12:22.391 --> 12:23.299
What the hell?!

12:23.392 --> 12:26.077
But, Dad,
Homer has a good heart,

12:26.079 --> 12:28.246
and I'm going to marry him.

12:28.248 --> 12:30.231
Oh, honey, this Simpson fellow
will never provide for you.

12:30.233 --> 12:33.101
He has jackass written
all over him.

12:33.103 --> 12:35.736
Marge, do you have
any turpentine?

12:35.738 --> 12:37.505
It's not coming off.

12:37.832 --> 12:39.816
Hmm.

12:39.818 --> 12:43.002
His friends did that
after he fell asleep at a party.

12:43.004 --> 12:46.005
Homer's the sweetest person
I've ever met.

12:46.007 --> 12:47.490
Every time I look into his eyes,

12:47.492 --> 12:50.918
I see someone who will
never stop loving me.

12:50.920 --> 12:53.921
Oh... crap.

12:53.923 --> 12:56.332
Look, I'm gonna leave you
something special in my will

12:56.334 --> 12:58.167
to make sure you're okay,
because you've found

12:58.169 --> 12:59.927
every father's worst nightmare:

12:59.929 --> 13:04.098
true love with a true loser.

13:04.100 --> 13:07.026
Loser? But I thought
Marge's dad liked me.

13:07.028 --> 13:08.936
He was always warning me about

13:08.938 --> 13:10.955
doors hitting my butt
on the way out.

13:10.957 --> 13:13.107
How dare he emasculate me
from beyond the grave?

13:13.109 --> 13:16.795
Uh-huh. I told you
not to look at it.

13:16.797 --> 13:18.630
Wait, how could I remember
that talk

13:18.632 --> 13:21.299
between Marge and her dad
if I wasn't around to see it?

13:21.301 --> 13:24.636
You can see stuff like that
'cause you're a ghost now.

13:24.638 --> 13:26.471
You dead.

13:28.033 --> 13:29.456
(ghostlike):
D'oh...!

13:29.458 --> 13:31.384
I tried to tell you,
and you didn't want to hear me.

13:31.386 --> 13:35.204
You was eating your feelings
and carrying on.

13:35.206 --> 13:37.148
Goobie-Woo knows what's good.

13:38.226 --> 13:40.527
I'm gonna see this
in every dream now.

13:44.232 --> 13:46.566
Oh, my God, I'm in heaven now.

13:46.568 --> 13:49.052
It's so huge, so majestic.

13:49.054 --> 13:50.662
So red.

13:52.481 --> 13:55.149
Ooh, it's one of heaven's
goaty-footed angels.

13:55.151 --> 13:56.650
And look at that giant fork.

13:56.652 --> 14:00.654
Probably for eating
delicious, heavenly s'mores.

14:00.656 --> 14:02.231
Think again, pally.

14:02.233 --> 14:03.842
-(flesh sizzles)
-Ow!

14:03.844 --> 14:05.492
Wait a second, I'm in hell?
But why?

14:05.494 --> 14:08.329
Because you committed
the deadly sin of wrath

14:08.331 --> 14:10.664
against your father-in-law.

14:10.666 --> 14:14.168
So what? Everybody hates
everybody these days.

14:14.170 --> 14:16.262
Plus the rest of
the seven deadly sins

14:16.264 --> 14:19.357
all in the last half second
of your life.

14:19.359 --> 14:21.442
♪

14:33.098 --> 14:35.114
Whoo-hoo! I hit for the cycle!

14:35.116 --> 14:37.191
Okay, so this is
where you check in

14:37.193 --> 14:39.526
for your eternal punishments.

14:39.528 --> 14:40.027
Who are they?

14:40.029 --> 14:42.622
(lively chatter)

14:42.624 --> 14:45.608
That's our exchange program
we have with heaven.

14:45.610 --> 14:47.777
We send them people
condemned for sins

14:47.779 --> 14:48.961
that aren't sins anymore.

14:49.055 --> 14:51.464
<i> FEMALE ANNOUNCER:</i>
<i> All aboard for those damned</i>

14:51.466 --> 14:56.135
<i> for being gay between 5000 BC</i>
<i> and like ten years ago.</i>

14:56.137 --> 14:57.303
-It's about damn time.
-(all cheer)

14:57.305 --> 14:59.213
Make way for Miss Thing!

15:00.625 --> 15:02.883
<i> FEMALE ANNOUNCER:</i>
<i> Now arriving,</i>
<i> former residents of heaven</i>

15:02.885 --> 15:06.295
<i> who are now considered bad</i>
<i> by today's standards.</i>

15:06.297 --> 15:08.055
Wherefore art I in hell?

15:08.057 --> 15:09.465
I gave the world<i> Othello.</i>

15:09.467 --> 15:12.559
Yeah, and performed it
in blackface.

15:12.561 --> 15:14.078
Get outta here.

15:14.080 --> 15:15.304
(fierce growling)

15:15.306 --> 15:17.731
I didn't even actually
write the plays!

15:17.733 --> 15:21.144
Okay, Mr. Simpson,
looks like your punishment is

15:21.146 --> 15:22.495
to be boiled alive
for all eternity

15:22.497 --> 15:24.664
-in a lake of blood.
-All right.

15:24.666 --> 15:25.924
Just wait over there.

15:25.926 --> 15:28.426
Oh, there's a line?

15:30.413 --> 15:32.096
Hey, do you mind if
I go ahead of you?

15:32.098 --> 15:34.140
Yeah, in fact, I do mind.

15:37.328 --> 15:40.730
Oh, for... Oh... (groaning)

15:43.259 --> 15:44.609
Fine, take this buzzer.

15:44.611 --> 15:46.202
When we're ready for you,
it'll electrocute you

15:46.204 --> 15:47.946
and set your torso aflame!

15:47.948 --> 15:50.865
I know how buzzers work.

15:51.767 --> 15:54.010
(people screaming, crying out)

15:54.012 --> 15:57.196
Ooh, poker.

15:57.198 --> 15:59.606
Oh, boy, I got-a the best hand.

15:59.608 --> 16:01.017
I'm-a gonna win.

16:01.019 --> 16:02.018
Ha! Nice bluff, Benito.

16:02.020 --> 16:04.796
(laughter)

16:04.798 --> 16:08.633
Marge's dead dad!

16:08.635 --> 16:11.377
(grunting)

16:11.379 --> 16:13.362
You thought
I wasn't worthy of Marge.

16:13.364 --> 16:15.198
I'll kill you
and send you to super-hell!

16:15.200 --> 16:16.975
Hey, hey, behave yourself.

16:16.977 --> 16:19.702
We have standards here.

16:19.704 --> 16:21.220
Shut up, Tom Selleck!

16:21.222 --> 16:23.314
What Marge's dad did to me
was super-sucky.

16:23.316 --> 16:26.375
It's probably the reason
he ended up here.

16:26.377 --> 16:28.060
Actually, he ended up here
thanks to an unrelated

16:28.062 --> 16:30.304
check forging scheme.

16:30.306 --> 16:33.324
Checks. Remember them?
(chuckles)

16:33.326 --> 16:35.184
Oh, crazy.

16:35.186 --> 16:37.144
Homer, uh, let's you and me
take a walk.

16:37.146 --> 16:40.239
Walking?
Oh, this really is hell.

16:40.241 --> 16:42.583
-I want to show you something.
-(man groaning)

16:44.896 --> 16:46.579
Wow, another screen?

16:46.581 --> 16:50.249
Yeah, this is hell.
Screens everywhere.

16:50.251 --> 16:53.511
Mom, Dad, I'd like you
to meet Mercer.

16:53.513 --> 16:55.162
He designs board games.

16:55.164 --> 16:57.256
Oh, like Parker Brothers?

16:57.258 --> 17:00.259
(laughs)
Yeah, like Parker Brothers. No.

17:00.261 --> 17:03.354
You actually play that
mainstream corporate garbage?

17:03.356 --> 17:06.098
You're so lucky
to be meeting me today.

17:06.100 --> 17:08.175
Seriously, I am
so jealous of you.

17:08.177 --> 17:09.418
Check this out.

17:09.420 --> 17:12.196
My new game
is gonna be a huge hit.

17:13.366 --> 17:15.424
It combines the Stratego-ness
of Stratego,

17:15.426 --> 17:18.611
the implicit sexual tension
of Twister,

17:18.613 --> 17:21.873
and the hard-driving whimsy
of Tic-Tac-Toe.

17:21.875 --> 17:24.100
It's called Side-gammon.

17:24.102 --> 17:27.128
Who's up for a game? Huh?

17:28.439 --> 17:30.030
Oh, come on!

17:30.032 --> 17:31.440
It's super complicated!

17:31.442 --> 17:33.367
You'll be out
before you know it,

17:33.369 --> 17:35.444
and you'll be humiliated!

17:35.446 --> 17:37.889
(growls angrily) Excuse me,
I have to go yell something

17:37.891 --> 17:40.283
into your washer-dryer.

17:40.285 --> 17:43.227
He really is brilliant,
and he has a good heart.

17:43.229 --> 17:44.711
-I'm going to marry him.
-(door closes)

17:44.713 --> 17:46.972
MERCER (in other room):
I'm the Mozart of board games

17:46.974 --> 17:48.124
and novelties!

17:48.126 --> 17:51.460
Why, that guy's a total loser.

17:51.462 --> 17:53.479
I don't want him to marry Lisa.

17:53.481 --> 17:56.390
Wait, I was never as bad
as him, was I?

17:56.392 --> 17:59.468
(chuckles)
Actually, there was a time

17:59.470 --> 18:01.137
when I would have preferred
that guy to you.

18:01.139 --> 18:02.488
Plus, you know what?

18:02.490 --> 18:04.307
We got an advance copy
of Side-gammon,

18:04.309 --> 18:06.584
-and it's not bad.
-Oh, my God.

18:06.586 --> 18:09.312
I'm starting to see things
from another point of view.

18:09.314 --> 18:10.496
Your point of view.

18:10.498 --> 18:12.498
I didn't even know
other people had those.

18:12.500 --> 18:14.425
You were just worried
about Marge,

18:14.427 --> 18:16.094
the way I'd be worried
about Lisa.

18:16.096 --> 18:19.079
No matter how old
and dead we get,

18:19.081 --> 18:22.158
we just want to make sure
our little girls are okay.

18:22.160 --> 18:24.660
-(buzzer buzzing)
-D'oh!

18:24.662 --> 18:27.087
<i> FEMALE ANNOUNCER:</i>
<i> Homer Simpson,</i>
<i> we are now ready</i>

18:27.089 --> 18:29.256
<i> to boil you for eternity</i>
<i> in a lake of blood.</i>

18:29.258 --> 18:33.111
Wow, suddenly
that doesn't sound so good.

18:33.113 --> 18:35.446
(angelic choir sings)

18:35.448 --> 18:36.948
Eh, you just had
an epiphany, pally,

18:36.950 --> 18:38.524
which means you get
to go back to your life.

18:38.526 --> 18:42.936
It's a dumb rule, but we need
a two-thirds vote to change it.

18:42.938 --> 18:44.455
Which is also a dumb rule.

18:44.457 --> 18:46.682
What can I say?
Hell ain't perfect.

18:46.684 --> 18:48.701
Homer, you're getting
another chance.

18:48.703 --> 18:52.279
Now, get the hell out of hell
and go back to my daughter.

18:52.281 --> 18:55.691
You heard the man.
Let's get your ass home.

18:55.693 --> 18:56.259
(angelic choir sings)

18:58.504 --> 18:59.971
BOTH:
Ow!

18:59.973 --> 19:02.598
-Damn, that hurt.
-(groans)

19:05.127 --> 19:07.461
You died and went to hell.

19:07.463 --> 19:08.871
Ralph knows.

19:08.873 --> 19:10.481
Whee!

19:12.226 --> 19:13.317
Thank you, Goobie-Woo.

19:13.319 --> 19:15.969
I learned more
tumbling through the air

19:15.971 --> 19:18.881
than I ever did
tumbling through my life.

19:18.883 --> 19:20.992
-(tires screech)
-(siren whoops)

19:24.055 --> 19:25.997
-(gasps) Dad!
-Homer!

19:27.742 --> 19:30.075
Goobie-Woo. (giggles)

19:30.077 --> 19:32.819
Oh, Homie,
thank God you're okay.

19:32.821 --> 19:34.714
(Homer groaning)

19:38.920 --> 19:40.327
Homer, I have to ask you,

19:40.329 --> 19:43.723
why did you send me
that angry text?

19:46.019 --> 19:47.243
It doesn't matter.

19:47.245 --> 19:49.245
I have since set aside
my own ego

19:49.247 --> 19:51.580
and learned to savor
my many blessings.

19:51.582 --> 19:55.193
And you, my darling,
are foremost amongst them.

19:55.195 --> 19:58.103
I don't understand
a thing he's saying.

19:58.105 --> 20:00.531
(shouting gibberish)

20:02.760 --> 20:04.777
He seems to be in a lot of pain.

20:04.779 --> 20:06.278
Can't you give him something?

20:06.280 --> 20:07.430
Absolutely not.

20:07.432 --> 20:08.597
No can do till we get
to the hospital.

20:08.599 --> 20:11.784
(groaning)

20:11.786 --> 20:13.127
(Marge sighs)

20:16.457 --> 20:18.382
(sighs):
Ah.

20:18.384 --> 20:21.636
I guess I can go another month
without a new purse.

